{% # Exploration canvas v2.0.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v2.0.0 — drop `--content-width: 80rem` override and the `--exploration-bleed-extension` formula (no longer needed under the subgrid migration's named-line bleed grid; experimental blocks delegate positioning to section's grid-column rules). Keeps `--block-rhythm-*` defaults so blocks still inherit reasonable inter-block spacing.
  - v1.1.0 — initial structure (chrome sibling-of-content; production-native rendering)
{% endcomment %}

{% doc %}
  @description
  Shared render scaffold for every exploration section. Renders utility chrome (breadcrumb + intro) as a sibling of the validation content; the validation content is `{{ contents }}` emitted directly under `<token-section>` with no exploration-imposed wrapper. Validation blocks position via section's named-line bleed grid like any production block.

  Utility chrome carries its own width discipline (`.exploration__intro` with max-inline-size + padding). It does NOT cascade onto sibling validation content.

  @param {section} section - The section object (passed explicitly because snippets run in isolated scope)
  @param {string} contents - Pre-rendered child blocks markup. Sections capture `{% content_for 'blocks' %}` before rendering this snippet (snippets can't host `content_for`).

  Variables emitted (scoped to section's #base_selector):
  - `--block-rhythm-mobile` / `--block-rhythm-desktop`: 1rem / 1.5rem — production sections set these via the `spacing` metaobject; exploration uses reasonable defaults so blocks have inter-block spacing via the token-section block-rhythm cascade.

  Temporary scaffold — see BACKLOG.md § Active exploration.

  @example {% render 'exploration--canvas', section: section, contents: contents %}
{% enddoc %}

{% liquid
  assign base_selector = 'shopify-section-' | append: section.id
%}

<token-section data-modifiers="theme-root">
  {% render 'exploration--breadcrumb' %}

  <header class='exploration__intro'>
    <h1>{{ section.settings.title }}</h1>
    <p>{{ section.settings.description }}</p>
  </header>

  {{ contents }}
</token-section>

{% capture dynamic_style %}
  --block-rhythm-mobile: 1rem;
  --block-rhythm-desktop: 1.5rem;
{% endcapture %}
{% render 'utility--dynamic-style', base_selector: base_selector, css_content: dynamic_style %}
